<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Lab: Access Network-Attached Storage</h1>
  </header>
  <main>
    <nav>
      <a href="index.html">&larr; Back to LVM Lab</a>
    </nav>

    <h2>Objective</h2>
    <p>Configure the automounter with an indirect map, using exports from an NFSv4 server.</p>

    <h2>Outcomes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Install required packages to set up the automounter.</li>
      <li>Configure an automounter indirect map with NFSv4 resources.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Preparation</h2>
    <pre><code>[student@workstation ~]$ lab start netstorage-review</code></pre>

    <h2>Environment Overview</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>serverb</code> shares <code>/shares</code> containing <code>management</code>, <code>production</code>, and <code>operation</code>.</li>
      <li><code>servera</code> must automount them under <code>/remote</code>.</li>
      <li>Groups and users have specific read/write permissions for each export.</li>
      <li>All user passwords: <code>redhat</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Step 1: Log in and Install Packages</h2>
    <pre><code>[student@workstation ~]$ ssh student@servera
[student@servera ~]$ sudo -i
[root@servera ~]# dnf install autofs
Is this ok [y/N]: y
Complete!</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 2: Test NFS Access</h2>
    <pre><code>[root@servera ~]# mount -t nfs serverb.lab.example.com:/shares /mnt
[root@servera ~]# ls -l /mnt
drwxrwx---. 2 root managers   25 Apr  4 01:13 management
drwxrwx---. 2 root operators  25 Apr  4 01:13 operation
drwxrwx---. 2 root production 25 Apr  4 01:13 production
[root@servera ~]# umount /mnt</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 3: Configure Automounter</h2>
    <pre><code># Master map
[root@servera ~]# vi /etc/auto.master.d/shares.autofs
/remote  /etc/auto.shares

# Indirect map
[root@servera ~]# vi /etc/auto.shares
* -rw,sync,fstype=nfs4 serverb.lab.example.com:/shares/&
</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 4: Start & Enable autofs</h2>
    <pre><code>[root@servera ~]# systemctl enable --now autofs
Created symlink /etc/systemd/system/multi-user.target.wants/autofs.service â†’ /usr/lib/systemd/system/autofs.service.</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 5: Verify Automount</h2>
    <p>Test as different users to ensure correct NFS permissions.</p>

    <h3>Manager Test</h3>
    <pre><code>[root@servera ~]# su - manager1
[manager1@servera ~]$ ls /remote/management
Welcome.txt
[manager1@servera ~]$ echo TEST1 > /remote/management/Test.txt
[manager1@servera ~]$ cat /remote/management/Test.txt
TEST1
</code></pre>

    <h3>DB User Test</h3>
    <pre><code>[root@servera ~]# su - dbuser1
[dbuser1@servera ~]$ ls /remote/production
Welcome.txt
[dbuser1@servera ~]$ echo TEST2 > /remote/production/Test.txt
[dbuser1@servera ~]$ cat /remote/production/Test.txt
TEST2
</code></pre>

    <h3>Contractor Test</h3>
    <pre><code>[root@servera ~]# su - contractor1
[contractor1@servera ~]$ ls /remote/operation
Welcome.txt
[contractor1@servera ~]$ echo TEST3 > /remote/operation/Test.txt
[contractor1@servera ~]$ cat /remote/operation/Test.txt
TEST3
</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 6: Check Mounted Exports</h2>
    <pre><code>[root@servera ~]# mount | grep nfs
serverb.lab.example.com:/shares/management on /remote/management type nfs4 (...)
serverb.lab.example.com:/shares/operation on /remote/operation type nfs4 (...)
serverb.lab.example.com:/shares/production on /remote/production type nfs4 (...)
</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 7: Evaluation & Finish</h2>
    <pre><code>[student@workstation ~]$ lab grade netstorage-review
[student@workstation ~]$ lab finish netstorage-review</code></pre>

